SIMPLE: reject
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reject
<hw>Re*ject"</hw> <pr>(r?-j?kt")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Rejected</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Rejecting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>rejectus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>reicere</ets>, <ets>rejicere</ets>;
pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>jacere</ets> to throw: cf. F.
<ets>rejeter</ets>, formerly also spelt <ets>rejecter</ets>. See
<er>Jet</er> a shooting forth.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cast from one;
to throw away; to discard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Therefore all this exercise of hunting . . . the Utopians have
<qex>rejected</qex> to their butchers.</q> <rj><qau>Robynson (More's
Utopia).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Reject</qex> me not from among thy children.</q>
<rj><qau>Wisdom ix. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To refuse to receive or to acknowledge; to decline
haughtily or harshly; to repudiate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That golden scepter which thou didst <qex>reject</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Because thou hast <qex>rejected</qex> knowledge, I will also
<qex>reject</qex> thee, that thou shalt be no priest to me.</q>
<rj><qau>Hos. iv. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To refuse to grant; <as>as, to <ex>reject</ex> a
prayer or request</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To repel; renounce; discard; rebuff; refuse;
decline.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rejectable</ent>⟦br⟧
